CORONAVIRUS disease 2019 (COVID-19) has so far resulted to more than 11,000 deaths globally. By Saturday afternoon, BBC reported that confirmed cases are over 275,000 with nearly 90,000 been recovered. Spain death toll has jumped by more than 300 to 1,326, another grim record for the Europen country. It is predicted by the BBC that one in five Americans “soon to be under 'stay at home' order.” Meanwhile, after months fighting the virus, Singapore has finally report first two deaths caused by the deadly Coronavirus. The Saturday report said that China has not registered new locally-transmitted cases for a third consecutive day While Sydney closed its famous beaches, including Bondi, due to overcrowding, Britain wakes up to shuttered pubs, restaurants and cafes. 